<scriptment id="73000" point="atomic_simulation" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-10-16" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>At house, Yuki sits on her bed, holding her head, Nozomi patting her back.</narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">This is so wrong!</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">The Clan is making me feel!</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Call of Duty on hundred-foot screens shall never jar a man as Actual Modern Warfare.</line>
		<line id="4000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">If simulation is to impact man, it must move from pixel-perfection to atom-perfection!</line>
		<narration>Yuki stands.</narration>
		<line id="5000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Atomic Simulation brings the burden of permanency!</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Atomic Simulation ceases the dissociation	 between player and game!</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Not this travesty Jacques is committing.</line>
		<narration>Yuki cries.</narration>
		<line id="8000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Is this game becoming more real than me?</line>
		<line id="9000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">No. To become real, I must do something real.</line>
		<line id="10000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Nozomi, I have a plan.</line>
		<narration>Yuki whispers into Nozomi's ear. Nozomi gasps and smiles. Nozomi commences text-messaging.<comment>If the Player zooms into the screen, Yuki bats her away.</comment></narration>
	</part>
</scriptment>